===3D修復版===
On August 29, 2016 (August 29, 1997, being the date when Skynet becomes self-aware in the films), it was announced that the film would be digitally remastered in 3D to commemorate its 25th anniversary, with a worldwide re-release planned for summer 2017. The version to be remastered and rereleased in 3D was the original 137 minute theatrical cut, as the extended edition is not James Cameron's preferred version. Multiple camera shots from the opening chase sequence were digitally altered to fix a minor continuity error which had bugged Cameron since the 1991 release.<ref name="T23D">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/terminator-2-3d-release-set-849272|title=James Cameron, DMG Partner for 'Terminator 2' 3D Re-Release Targeting China (Exclusive)|author=Patrick Brzeski|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=2015-12-15|access-date=2015-12-16}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Entertainment Tonight|title=EXCLUSIVE: The One Scene James Cameron Changed in 'Terminator 2' Re-Release: 'It Just Bugged Me'|date=2017-08-11|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wpXkN-uVYY0|accessdate=2018-03-16|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813075159/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wpXkN-uVYY0|archivedate=2017-08-13}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=2017年9月}} [[DMG_Entertainment|DMG Entertainment]] and [[StudioCanal|StudioCanal]] worked together with Cameron to convert the film using the StereoD technology.<ref name="T23D"/> The 3D version premiered on February 17, 2017, at the [[Berlin_International_Film_Festival|Berlin International Film Festival]], with the theatrical re-release being scheduled for August 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/programm/berlinale_programm/datenblatt.php?film_id=201702490#tab=filmStills|title=Terminator 2: Judgement Day 3D at Berlinale|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170323054958/https://www.berlinale.de/en/programm/berlinale_programm/datenblatt.php?film_id=201702490#tab=filmStills|archivedate=2017-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/terminator-2-3d-release-date/|title=Terminator 2 3D Release Date Confirmed for Late Summer 2017|date=2017-03-03|work=Slashfilm|access-date=2017-08-12|language=en-US|archive-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824230359/http://www.slashfilm.com/terminator-2-3d-release-date|dead-url=no}}</ref> Similar to Cameron's ''[[Titanic_(1997_film)|Titanic 3D]]'', [[Lightstorm_Entertainment|Lightstorm Entertainment]] oversaw the work on the 3D version of ''Terminator 2'', which took around 1800 artists about eight months to finish.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vfxvoice.com/converting-a-classic-how-stereo-d-gave-terminator-2-judgement-day-a-3d-makeover/|title=Converting a Classic: How Stereo D Gave Terminator 2: Judgment Day a 3D Makeover|author=Ian Failes|website=VFX Voice|date=2017-08-24|access-date=2018-03-20|archive-date=2018-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180325185003/http://vfxvoice.com/converting-a-classic-how-stereo-d-gave-terminator-2-judgement-day-a-3d-makeover/|dead-url=no}}</ref> The restoration was released by Distrib Films US, a company which typically distributes foreign films. The studio released the film exclusively for one week in [[AMC_Theatres|AMC Theatres]] nationwide, and said that it will expand depending on the film's performances in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/james-cameron-terminator-2-jack-lowden-england-is-mine-specialty-box-office-1202156290/amp/|title=3D 'Terminator 2' Invades AMC Theaters; Jack Lowden Is Morrissey In 'England Is Mine' – Specialty Box Office Preview|author=Brian Brooks|website=''[[Deadline_Hollywood|Deadline Hollywood]]''|date=2017-08-25|access-date=2017-08-26|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170825195744/http://deadline.com/2017/08/james-cameron-terminator-2-jack-lowden-england-is-mine-specialty-box-office-1202156290/amp/|archivedate=2017-08-25}}</ref>

The 3D version opened Friday, August 25, 2017, across 371 theaters (or 463 3D auditoriums), earning $552,773 in its opening weekend, averaging $1,490 per screen;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?view=&yr=2017&wknd=34&p=.htm|title=August 25 – 27, 2017|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=2017-08-29|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828201044/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?view=&yr=2017&wknd=34&p=.htm|archivedate=2017-08-28}}</ref> this was considered an amount lower than what other '80s and '90s re-releases earned in their respective opening weekends such as ''[[Top_Gun|Top Gun]]'' ($1.9 million, which also played in IMAX), ''[[Raiders_of_the_Lost_Ark|Raiders of the Lost Ark]]'' ($1.6 million), as well as more high-profile reissues of ''Titanic'', ''[[The_Lion_King|The Lion King]]'' and ''Jurassic Park'' over the last several years. During its opening weekend, ''Titanic 3D'' grossed $17.3 million in 2,674 theaters, averaging $6,464 in April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/beach-rats-box-office-terminator-2-return-specialty-1202157025/amp/|title='Beach Rats' Seduces In Debut, 'Terminator 2: Judgment Day 3D' Starts Slow – Specialty Box Office|author=Brian Brooks|website=''Deadline Hollywood''|date=2017-08-27|accessdate=2017-08-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827224219/http://deadline.com/2017/08/beach-rats-box-office-terminator-2-return-specialty-1202157025/amp/|archivedate=2017-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/26/box-office-leap-birth-of-the-dragon-and-terminator-2-all-bomb-on-friday/amp/|title=Box Office: 'Leap,' 'Birth Of The Dragon' And 'Terminator 2' All Bomb On Friday|author=Scott Mendelson|website=''Forbes''|date=2017-08-26|accessdate=2017-08-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826175822/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/26/box-office-leap-birth-of-the-dragon-and-terminator-2-all-bomb-on-friday/amp/|archivedate=2017-08-26}}</ref> While not major contributing factors, the release performance of the film is thought to have suffered from coinciding with [[Hurricane_Harvey|Hurricane Harvey]], which eased moviegoing admissions in many parts of the country, the much anticipated [[Floyd_Mayweather_Jr._vs._Conor_McGregor|boxing fight between Floyd Mayweather Jr. and Conor McGregor]], and the [[Game_of_Thrones_(season_7)|season 7]] finale of ''[[Game_of_Thrones|Game of Thrones]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/27/box-office-leap-tops-weak-newbies-terminator-2-stumbles-in-3d/|title=Box Office: 'Leap' Tops Weak Newbies, 'Terminator 2' Stumbles In 3D|author=Scott Mendelson|website=''Forbes''|date=2017-08-27|accessdate=2017-08-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827171739/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/27/box-office-leap-tops-weak-newbies-terminator-2-stumbles-in-3d/|archivedate=2017-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/hitmans-bodyguard-birth-of-the-dragon-leap-all-saints-low-summer-box-office-weekend-mayweather-mcgregor-fight-1202156230/|title=Don't Blame Hurricane Harvey & Showtime Fight For Weekend's Lousy Box Office: Distribs Served Up Lackluster Titles|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=''Deadline Hollywood''|date=2017-08-27|accessdate=2017-08-28|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828100820/http://deadline.com/2017/08/hitmans-bodyguard-birth-of-the-dragon-leap-all-saints-low-summer-box-office-weekend-mayweather-mcgregor-fight-1202156230/|archivedate=2017-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/28/game-of-thrones-didnt-cause-the-worst-box-office-frame-in-16-years|title='Game Of Thrones' Didn't Cause The Worst Box Office Frame In 16 Years|author=Scott Mendelson|website=''Forbes''|date=2017-08-28|accessdate=2017-08-29|archive-date=2018-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811165007/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/08/28/game-of-thrones-didnt-cause-the-worst-box-office-frame-in-16-years|dead-url=no}}</ref>
{{TransF}}

===家庭媒体===
本片于1997年8月首次发行单碟DVD，片长为139分钟。1993年11月24日，《终结者2：审判日：特别剪辑版》发行了[[VHS|录像带]]和[[激光影碟|激光影碟]]，其中包含有17分钟之前未放映过的内容，包含迈克尔·比恩客串出演的场景。不过，1992年，本片也发行了与最初上映时完全一致的版本。而之后发行的“最终版”和“至尊版”DVD同样也包括了这些镜头。<ref name=DF.com>{{cite web|title=Terminator 2|url=http://www.dynamicforces.com/htmlfiles/infodatabase.html?showInfodatabase=NS04110732220|publisher=Dynamic Forces|accessdate=2013-05-04|archive-date=2012-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826041542/http://www.dynamicforces.com/htmlfiles/infodatabase.html?showInfodatabase=NS04110732220|dead-url=no}}</ref>

至尊版的DVD拥有多个针对电脑DVD-ROM光盘驱动器的功能，包括渗透模拟器单元和T2 FX工作室，这个功能可以将任何一个人的肖像导入并演变为片中两位終結者的新形象。另外还有一个名为“天网战场设计”的程序，可以让用户自主设计其战斗机械，并在线进行追踪等操作。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/t2extreme.php |title=DVD Verdict Review – Terminator 2: Judgment Day: Extreme Edition |author=Skipper, Elizabeth |publisher=DVD Verdict |date=2003-06-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224021812/http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/t2extreme.php |archivedate=2008-12-24 }}</ref>至尊版DVD同时还拥有一个全[[1080p|1080p]]高清质量的WMV-HD格式剧场版电影，这也是本片首次发行[[Full_HD|Full HD]]（全高清）格式q。

2006年，{{link-en|狮门家庭娱乐公司|Lionsgate Home Entertainment}}发布了本片的[[蓝光|蓝光]]影碟，其中提供1080P全高清视频和DTS 5.1声道无损音频，但没有其它特别内容。<ref>{{cite web|author=Bracke, Peter M.|title=Terminator 2: Judgment Day – Skynet Edition (Blu-ray)|publisher=Highdefdigest.com|url=http://bluray.highdefdigest.com/2152/terminator2_skynet.html|date=2009-5-7, 2009|accessdate=2013-02-18|archive-date=2012-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122065902/http://bluray.highdefdigest.com/2152/terminator2_skynet.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年5月19日，狮门再次发行了改进的蓝光影碟，其中主要是音频升级为THX认证的DTS 6.1声道高保真无损音频。这次发行的“天网剪辑版”（SkyNet Edition）也出现在限量收藏版包装中，限量收藏版中包括了之前的最终版和至尊版DVD的全部内容。<ref>{{cite news|author=Peter, Sciretta|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/cool-stuff-limited-edition-terminator-2-complete-collectors-set//|title=Cool Stuff: Limited Edition Terminator 2 Complete Collector's Set|work=Slashfilm.com|date=2009-03-23|accessdate=2013-02-18|archive-date=2011-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110813025058/http://www.slashfilm.com/cool-stuff-limited-edition-terminator-2-complete-collectors-set/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{TransH}}
2017年7月，该电影发布了两款新的蓝光版本。首先是4K 修复版，然后是于2017年8月发布的3D转换版本的蓝光3D。这些重新发行的影片将包括新的临时演员，包括预告片、纪录片制作和“剧场版、导演版和特别加长版中删减的分支剧情”。此外，还发布了“Endo-arm特别版”捆绑包，包括3D和4K版本，以及CD音轨。[68] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=21710|title=StudioCanal: Remastered Terminator 2 Prepped for 4K Blu-ray, 3D/2D Blu-ray Also Coming Up|publisher=Blu-ray.com|date=2017-07-18|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170718220701/http://www.blu-ray.com/news/?id=21710|archivedate=2017-07-18}}</ref>

====加長版====
2015年，索尼发布了《终结者4》的加长版，作为《终结者4》套装的一部分，包含了前四部《终结者》电影。但是，它不包含任何特别花絮。随后发行的“终极版”和“极限版”DVD也包括了电影的扩展版。[64]<ref name=DF.com/>

除了其他大量被重新删除的场景，加长版还有一个不同的结局，在2029年，年迈的莎拉·康纳看着成年的美国参议员约翰和他的女儿在华盛顿的操场上玩耍，讲述审判日从来没有发生过。[69]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/terminator-2-unused-epilogue-gave-794534|title='Terminator 2' Unused Epilogue Gave Everyone the Happy Ending They Wanted (Video)|author=Graeme McMillan|work=[[The_Hollywood_Reporter|The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=([[Prometheus_Global_Media|Prometheus Global Media]])|date=2015-05-08|accessdate=2015-05-09|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510192932/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/terminator-2-unused-epilogue-gave-794534|archivedate=2015-05-10}}</ref> 这部电影的加长版本也包括在“天网版”蓝光光碟中。
{{TransF}}

==市场营销==
[[File:Terminator_2_-_3D_Entrance_Universal_Studios_Florida.jpg|thumb]]环球影城的“T2 3-D: Battle Across Time”入口。|alt=位于佛罗里达州环球影城的3D版終結者2入口]]

[[漫威出版公司|漫威出版公司]]根据影片改编了3个系列的动漫作品，电影上映后，有多个根据该片改编的动漫书籍也开始发行，如Malibu Comics出版的《{{Nowrap|Terminator 2 – Judgment Day: Cybernetic Dawn}}》、《{{Nowrap|Terminator 2 – Judgment Day: Nuclear Twilight}}》，IDW Comics出版的《{{Nowrap|T2: Infiltrator}}》和《{{Nowrap|T2: Rising Storm}}》，S.M. Stirling的《{{Nowrap|T2: Future War'}}》和Russell Blackford的《{{Nowrap|The John Connor Chronicles}}》。

1996年，詹姆斯·卡梅伦为[[环球主题乐园及度假村|环球影城主题公园]]导演了一个名为“T2 3-D: Battle Across Time”的3D电影短片，其中可以看到阿诺德、琳达、罗伯特、爱德华分别回归他们所扮演的角色。这段全长仅12分钟的短片耗资高达6千万美元，是电影史上平均每分钟造价最昂贵的影片。<ref>{{cite news| title = Terminator 2: 3-D| author = Robert, Firsching| work = New York Times| url = http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/137655/Terminator-2-3-D/overview| quote = This 12-minute short [...] cost $60 million to produce, making it the most expensive venture per minute in movie history.| accessdate = 2013-02-23| archive-date = 2012-11-07| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121107051036/http://movies.nytimes.com/movie/137655/Terminator-2-3-D/overview| dead-url = no}}</ref>这一短片于1996年中期在佛罗里达环球影城推出，1999年5月在好莱坞环球影城推出，2001年3月在日本环球影城推出。<ref>{{cite web|title=Terminator 2 3D|url=http://www.dvdvision.fr/jco/T23D.htm|publisher=DVD Vision|accessdate=2012-01-10|archive-date=2020-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200625162304/http://www.dvdvision.fr/jco/T23D.htm|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==原声带==
